    public interface LTSminMealy<I,​O,​R>
extends ModelChecker.MealyModelChecker<I,​O,​String,​R>, LTSmin<I,​MealyMachine<?,​I,​?,​O>,​R>
    A feature of this ModelChecker, is that one can remove particular output symbols from the given MealyMachine hypothesis. This is useful when those symbols are actually symbols representing system deadlocks. When checking LTL formulae special attention has to be given to deadlock situations.
